      "content": "When people talk about a sinking ship, they usually mean a leaky one that can still be safely docked, not an anode that can never be fixed, though you can never fix a whole entire universe sleeve so that remains an overwhelming feeling of helplessness. There is also the perspective that you are fighting true hard ship while also fighting the collapse of your own mind to try to stop the bleeding. You don't have to save the world; you can just try to save yourself and your house while you figure out the bigger picture. Do you feel you have enough support right now?",
