      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That exhaustion is an incredibly heavy burden to carry when the prospettiva feels like the sky is falling. While it can feel logical to abandon a hopeless situation, staying until you find the last ounce of peace or even sleep is often just as destructive as giving up entirely. Sometimes the most resilient act isn't fighting the fire, but finding the sheer will to rest and breathe before the world gets too dark to see anything else. Is there anything you want to do today just to get you through the night, no matter how small it is?",
